{
 "name": "RPlog_Escape",
 "title": "Escape",
 "summary": "Bruised from interrogation and held in a stark white cell aboard the Imperial vessel Broadsword, the green Twi'lek prisoner Tal'sin seizes his chance when Captain Lynae Caiton arrives with a staff officer to skim the last of his information before his planned 're-education'. Tal'sin body-checks Caiton, re-breaking her already-injured left arm, wrests away her blaster, and kills the lieutenant, then ambushes the responding stormtroopers, strangling and shooting them before forcing the captain to unlock his stun cuffs. Donning a dead trooper's armor, he marches the wounded Caiton through the ship as if escorting an injured prisoner. To spare further bloodshed, Caiton strikes a deal: she will fly him out using her command codes if he kills no more of her men, and she guides them to an unprovisioned medical shuttle and launches it one-handed from the Broadsword. Once clear and jumped toward Coruscant, Tal'sin honors the bargain by declaring her free, but then cuffs her to the shuttle's bulkhead, smirking that her captors might pay him too, the escape complete with the captain now his bargaining chip.",
